# Multi-agent Communications Framework Sprint Tracking Standard

This rule defines the standardized approach for tracking sprint progress within any project using the Multi-agent Communications Framework. It establishes file locations, naming conventions, and document structures that should be followed regardless of the specific project or workspace.

## Source of Truth Files

Each project workspace must maintain these standard files:

| Information Type | Standard Location | Format |
|------------------|------------------|--------|
| Sprint Status | `docs/sprint-status.md` | Markdown |
| Release Plan | `docs/technical/RELEASE_PLAN.md` | Markdown |
| User Stories | `docs/user-stories/{area}/{US-ID}-{name}.md` | Markdown |

## File Structure and Naming

### Sprint Status Document
- Location: `docs/sprint-status.md`
- Purpose: Single source of truth for current sprint status and progress
- Updates: Updated at the end of each day with current progress
- Content: All user stories in the current sprint, their status, acceptance criteria progress, and any blockers

### Release Plan Document
- Location: `docs/technical/RELEASE_PLAN.md`
- Purpose: Long-term planning and release schedule
- Updates: Updated at the beginning of each sprint and when major changes occur
- Content: Overall project timeline, sprint goals, and milestone definitions

### User Story Documents
- Location: `docs/user-stories/{area}/{US-ID}-{name}.md`
- Structure example: `docs/user-stories/core/US-C-001-plugin-setup.md`
- Areas: Defined by project requirements (e.g., `core`, `feature`, `integration`, etc.)
- Naming: `US-{AREA}-{NUMBER}-{kebab-case-name}.md`
- Content: User story description, acceptance criteria, tasks, implementation details, and test coverage

## Document Structures

Each document type must follow a standardized structure to ensure consistency across all projects using the Multi-agent Communications Framework.

### Sprint Status Structure
As defined in the `docs/SPRINT_TRACKING_STANDARD.md` document within each project workspace.

### User Story Structure
As defined in the `docs/user-stories/templates/user-story-template.md` document within each project workspace.

## Role Responsibilities

1. ES (Executive Secretary) is responsible for maintaining sprint documentation
2. SET (Software Engineering Team) maintains technical implementation details
3. CTW (Copy/Technical Writer) ensures documentation consistency
4. All roles should follow these standards in their respective areas 